CAPE TOWN - The Auditor-General has told Parliament that irregular expenditure at the Department of Water and Sanitation had rocketed to R6.4-billion. An executive at the AG’s office, Andries Sekgetho, said on Wednesday the irregular spending was significantly high in the 2014/15 and 2016/17 financial years. READ: MPs to decide scope of inquiry into Water and Sanitation Department It was now R2.4-billion higher than the R4-billion initially disclosed by the department. The undisclosed R2.4-billion in spending was discovered during an audit of the department. African News Agency